<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-01-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-01-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="439" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                        <head>439. Telegram 1475 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d439fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/1–1156.
                                Confidential; Niact; Limited Distribution. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_CRN_1">Clough</persName>.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-01-11">January 11, 1956, 7:01
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d439-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d439-1"/>
                        <p>1475. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>. Your 1353.</p>
                        <p>No public reply made to Peiping allegation.</p>
                        <p>If <persName corresp="#p_WP_1">Wang</persName> should raise subject you
                            should reply this is irresponsible charge similar to others made in past
                            and you do not intend to engage in discussion of it.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1"><hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>